Improvements to Lisp in this package
=====================================

  (To be found mainly in the file "bibliotek.macros.el".)
  (See especially the macros `deff' `varbind' and `fbind')

  This package contains a set of macros to circumvent one of the
  deficiencies of elisp, namely the fact that all elisp variables are
  what is called `special' in lisp terminology.  (To a much smaller
  extent, an analogous problem exists within true Common Lisp.)  My
  macros provide truly local variables for use within defined functions,
  which is important in the present setup in order to avoid a function's
  inadvertently changing the values of poset elements whose names it
  doesn't necessarily know.

  In addition the package defines, and utilizes, several macros to
  simplify the syntax of commonly used Lisp constructs.  For example,
  instead of writing, `(let ((x 3)) ...)' you can say simply 
  `(varbind x 3)'.

